						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying beside the Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1556 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1478, Naḷa, Āshāḍha ba. 13</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1556 A.D. July 4, Saturday.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged epigraph mentions several individuals such as Vijayanagaraṁ Chinna-Vīrayya, Kalyāṇaṁ Vīrayya, Jaṁgaṁ Vīrayya etc., who together seem to have made some gift to god Rāma of Rāyasamudram. Mentions Gajarāmanipalle and Jagatāpigutti-sīma.</p>						

						</summary>
